<common-name datatype='string'>trpR</common-name>
<comment datatype='string'>The expression of the &lt;i&gt;trpR&lt;/i&gt; gene is repressed threefold by the TrpR protein. This protein binds around the transcriptional start site of &lt;i&gt;trpR&lt;/i&gt;. Therefore, TrpR could minimally block the transcription initiation because the RNA polymerase could not bind to the promoter[&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/3050131&quot;&gt;Klig88&lt;/a&gt;].
&lt;p&gt;
The &lt;i&gt;trpLEDCBA&lt;/i&gt;, &lt;i&gt;aroH&lt;/i&gt;, and &lt;i&gt;trpR&lt;/i&gt; operons are coordinately regulated by the TrpR transcriptional repressor in response to intracellular levels of L-tryptophan ([&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/3315853&quot;&gt;Kumamoto87&lt;/a&gt;] and references therein). TrpR acts differently at each operator and binds to multiple helically stacked sites [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/3315853&quot;&gt;Kumamoto87&lt;/a&gt;].</comment>
